---
// src/components/PaidQuerySnapshot.astro
//
// Tiny inline script that snapshots window.location.search into a global
// (window.__BHQ_INBOUND_QUERY__) the instant the parser hits it. Mount
// inside <head>, IMMEDIATELY BEFORE the <Analytics /> component, so this
// script runs before the async gtag.js loader has a chance to consume
// gclid via the GA4 "URL parameter management" feature.
//
// Why this exists (deeply, after three failed attempts):
//
// Google Analytics 4 ships with a feature that strips gclid (and other
// auto-attribution params) from the visible URL via history.replaceState()
// shortly after gtag.js finishes loading. The stripping serves two
// purposes for Google: it prevents gclid from polluting bookmarks /
// shared links, and it migrates the click-id into a first-party cookie
// for cross-session attribution. The behavior is configurable in
// GA4 Admin → Data Streams → Configure tag settings → Adjust GCLID URL
// parameter behavior, but it's ON BY DEFAULT.
//
// Critically, the strip ALSO mutates the entry returned by
// `performance.getEntriesByType("navigation")[0].name`. The Performance
// Navigation Timing spec says `name` is the page's current document URL,
// which is updated on history.replaceState(). So our earlier "read from
// Navigation Timing entry to win the race" approach failed because the
// entry itself is mutated by GA4's strip, not just the URL bar.
//
// The only reliable fix is to capture the URL into a JS variable BEFORE
// gtag has a chance to run, and have downstream consumers read from
// that variable. This component is the capture; PaidTrafficHero.astro
// is the consumer.
//
// Mounting position matters: must be inside <head>, immediately before
// <Analytics />. That way the HTML parser executes this inline script
// synchronously before it even reaches the `<script async src="gtag/js">`
// tag, guaranteeing our snapshot writes the global before gtag could
// possibly start.
---

<script is:inline>
  // Snapshot the inbound URL query string the instant the parser hits
  // this script. Runs synchronously, blocks the parser for ~0.01ms,
  // completes long before gtag.js can load and strip gclid.
  window.__BHQ_INBOUND_QUERY__ = window.location.search || "";
</script>
